originalText.text: My son (newly 15) did the 6-week program and I thought it was very good for him. First of all, it gave him something to do this summer (no typical job due to COVID), and second, I think it made him think about things other than math, which is his favorite subject and thing to do! I also appreciated the one on one mentoring sessions in addition to the weekly group session. I also liked that he had homework to do between sessions. I thought that he received a lot of attention from the LogoLife founders and instructors and that the info given to him to develop was detailed and effective, and tailored to his passions. A productive and comprehensive teen entrepreneurship program.

originalText.text: My daughter (14) completed the GameChangers 3-day workshop, July 24-27, 2020. The program was REALLY good. The presenters were knowledgeable, and they pushed the participants to critically think. I can attest to the program being solid as I completed my dissertation on how emotional intelligence and grit impact academic success. I teach at a major University on many of the topics presented. Truthfully my daughter knew most of the information, but it was good to have her in an environment where it was discussed outside of me and to be able to hear the ideas and perspectives of peers and people outside of her social circle. In this case people she has never met. It was also great to have her make SMART Goals for her very near future and address her passion using the Dream Narrator.

originalText.text: My 15yo son took the 3 day webinar last week and loved it! He is the kind of kid that only wants to have fun and not work. So for him to say this was "great" was monumental. I was able to occasionally listen in and really loved the information the instructors were imparting. I even learned things from this that I didn't know. It was refreshing to have someone else tell my son what I have been telling him for years. It was difficult to refrain from saying, "I told you so". Thank you for backing us up as parents!
